IT Budget




Visteon Corporation is a global supplier of automotive systems, modules and components to global vehicle manufacturers and the automotive aftermarket. The company is primarily focused on producing climate, electronic, lighting, and interior products for vehicles.

In 2009, Visteon filed for Chapter… MoreVisteon Corporation is a global supplier of automotive systems, modules and components to global vehicle manufacturers and the automotive aftermarket. The company is primarily focused on producing climate, electronic, lighting, and interior products for vehicles.

In 2009, Visteon filed for Chapter 11 Bankruptcy protection. In the Fourth Quarter of 2010, the company exited bankruptcy protection and restructured. Visteon now has 26,000 employees with 1,200 employees in the US.
Visteon Corporation is a global supplier of automotive systems, modules and components to global vehicle manufacturers and the automotive aftermarket. The company is primarily focused on producing climate, electronic, lighting, and interior products for vehicles.

In 2009, Visteon filed for Chapter… MoreVisteon Corporation is a global supplier of automotive systems, modules and components to global vehicle manufacturers and the automotive aftermarket. The company is primarily focused on producing climate, electronic, lighting, and interior products for vehicles.

In 2009, Visteon filed for Chapter 11 Bankruptcy protection. In the Fourth Quarter of 2010, the company exited bankruptcy protection and restructured. Visteon now has 26,000 employees with 1,200 employees in the US.

The IT department at the Visteon Corporation is primarily centralized at the headquarters in Van Burren Township, MI.

The majority of this department was outsourced to IBM in a 10-year contract initiated in 2003. The responsibilities managed by IBM include mainframe support services, data centers, disaster recovery, and customer support centers. IBM has additionally subcontracted some of their responsibilities to companies such as Capgemini. Visteon has other outsourcing/vendor agreements with companies such as AT&T, Siemens, Verizon Business, SAP, Oracle, and others. The information technology staff employed by Visteon primarily manages these outsourced contracts. 

The majority of the IT staff within Visteon lead ERP solutions, applications development, data network management, and desktop support, as well as company's enterprise resource planning. Other staff focuses include global IT contracts, specifically contracting decisions as well as the audit of IT invoices. The department of IT strategic infrastructure includes managers in charge of eCAD/eCAE application support and eCAD engineering.

Visteon Corporation is in the early stages of both desktop and server virtualization and will be using Citrix for desktop virtualization and VMware for server virtualization. The company is currently 20 percent completed with both projects.





